WEBVTT

00:08:57.709 --> 00:09:01.228
reminding themselves why they were doing
this work in the first place.

00:09:01.252 --> 00:09:05.353
SA: So it's sort of like painting
your work on a bigger canvas

00:09:05.377 --> 00:09:09.647
helped them reframe their struggles
when they had them.

00:09:10.111 --> 00:09:13.900
So for example,
this person was a rug designer.

00:09:13.924 --> 00:09:17.081
And she said, "You know,
when you look at it,

00:09:17.105 --> 00:09:21.153
I work on my hands and knees
in my disgusting basement,

00:09:21.177 --> 00:09:22.420
but I don't care."

00:09:22.444 --> 00:09:27.375
And she went on to say, "Picasso
worked in some paint-strewn studio,

00:09:27.399 --> 00:09:29.145
and he's who he is.

00:09:29.169 --> 00:09:31.746
And I know I'm not ever going to be that,